H2502.meaning: <meaning>to <def>pull off</def>; hence (intensively) to <def>strip</def>, (reflex.) to <def>depart</def>; by implication, to <def>deliver</def>, <def>equip</def> (for fight); <def>present</def>, <def>strengthen</def></meaning>
H2502.usage: <usage>arm (self), (go, ready) armed (× man, soldier), deliver, draw out, make fat, loose, (ready) prepared, put off, take away, withdraw self.</usage>

H2503.source: <source>or <w pron="khay'-lets" xlit="Chêlets">חֵלֶץ</w>; from <w src="H2502">2502</w>; perhaps, strength;</source>

H2504.source: <source>from <w src="H2502">2502</w> (in the sense of <def>strength</def>); only in the dual;</source>

H2505.meaning: <meaning>to <def>be smooth</def> (figuratively); by implication (as smooth stones were used for lots) to <def>apportion</def> or <def>separate</def></meaning>
H2505.usage: <usage>deal, distribute, divide, flatter, give, (have, im-) part(-ner), take away a portion, receive, separate self, (be) smooth(-er).</usage>

H2508.source: <source>(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to <w src="H2505">2505</w>;</source>

H2513.usage: <usage>field, flattering(-ry), ground, parcel, part, piece of land (ground), plat, portion, slippery place, smooth (thing).</usage>

H2518.source: <source>or <w pron="khil-kee-yaw'-hoo" xlit="Chilqîyâhûw">חִלְקִיָּהוּ</w>; from <w src="H2506">2506</w> and <w src="H3050">3050</w>; <def>portion of Jah</def>;</source>

H2519.meaning: <meaning>properly, something <def>very smooth</def>; i.e. a <def>treacherous</def> spot; figuratively, <def>blandishment</def></meaning>

H2521.source: <source>from <w src="H2520">2520</w> and the plural of <w src="H6697">6697</w>, with the article inserted; smoothness of the rocks;</source>

H2526.source: <source>the same as <w src="H2525">2525</w>; hot (from the tropical habitat);</source>
H2526.meaning: <meaning><def>Cham</def>, a son of Noah; also (as a patronymic) his descendants or their country</meaning>

H2528.source: <source>(Aramaic) or <w pron="kham-aw'" xlit="chămâh">חֲמָה</w>; (Aramaic), corresponding to <w src="H2534">2534</w>;</source>

H2529.source: <source>or (shortened) <w pron="khay-maw'" xlit="chêmâh">חֵמָה</w>; from the same root as <w src="H2346">2346</w>;</source>

H2530.usage: <usage>beauty, greatly beloved, covet, delectable thing, (× great) delight, desire, goodly, lust, (be) pleasant (thing), precious (thing).</usage>

H2534.usage: <usage>anger, bottles, hot displeasure, furious(-ly, -ry), heat, indignation, poison, rage, wrath(-ful). See <w src="H2529">2529</w>.</usage>

H2536.source: <source>from <w src="H2535">2535</w> and <w src="H410">410</w>; anger of God;</source>

H2537.source: <source>or <w pron="kham-ee-tal'" xlit="Chămîyṭal">חֲמִיטַל</w>; from <w src="H2524">2524</w> and <w src="H2919">2919</w>; father-in-law of dew;</source>

H2540.meaning: <meaning><def>Chammon</def>, the name of two places in Palestine</meaning>

H2546.source: <source>from an unused root probably meaning, to lie low;</source>

H2552.usage: <usage>enflame self, get (have) heat, be (wax) hot, (be, wax) warm (self, at).</usage>

H2554.usage: <usage>make bare, shake off, violate, do violence, take away violently, wrong, imagine wrongfully.</usage>

H2555.usage: <usage>cruel(-ty), damage, false, injustice, × oppressor, unrighteous, violence (against, done), violent (dealing), wrong.</usage>

H2556.meaning: <meaning>to <def>be pungent</def>; i.e. in taste (<def>sour</def>, i.e. literally <def>fermented</def>, or figuratively, <def>harsh</def>), in color (<def>dazzling</def>)</meaning>

H2560.source: <source>a primitive root; also as denominative (from <w src="H2564">2564</w>)</source>
H2560.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>boil</def> up; hence, to <def>ferment</def> (with scum); to <def>glow</def> (with redness); to <def>smear</def> with pitch</meaning>

H2563.meaning: <meaning>properly, a <def>bubbling</def> up, i.e. of water, a <def>wave</def>; of earth, <def>mire</def> or <def>clay</def> (cement); also a <def>heap</def>; hence, a <def>chomer</def> or dry measure</meaning>

H2570.source: <source>from an unused root probably meaning, to be stout;</source>

H2571.source: <source>passive participle of the same as <w src="H2570">2570</w>;</source>

H2575.source: <source>a variation for the first part of <w src="H2576">2576</w>; hot springs;</source>

H2576.source: <source>from the plural of <w src="H2535">2535</w> and <w src="H1756">1756</w>; hot springs of Dor;</source>

H2578.source: <source>from <w src="H2574">2574</w> and <w src="H6678">6678</w>; Chamath of Tsobah; probably the same as <w src="H2574">2574</w></source>

H2579.source: <source>from <w src="H2574">2574</w> and <w src="H7237">7237</w>; Chamath of Rabbah; probably the same as <w src="H2574">2574</w>.</source>

H2581.meaning: <meaning><def>Chen</def>, a figurative name for an Israelite</meaning>

H2582.source: <source>probably from <w src="H2580">2580</w> and <w src="H1908">1908</w>; favor of Hadad;</source>

H2583.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>incline</def>; by implication, to <def>decline</def> (of the slanting rays of evening); specifically, to <def>pitch</def> a tent; generally to <def>encamp</def> (for abode or siege)</meaning>
H2583.usage: <usage>abide (in tents), camp, dwell, encamp, grow to an end, lie, pitch (tent), rest in tent.</usage>

H2586.meaning: <meaning><def>Chanun</def>, the name of an Ammonite and of two Israelites</meaning>

H2588.meaning: <meaning>properly, a <def>vault</def> or <def>cell</def> (with an arch); by implication, a <def>prison</def></meaning>

H2592.source: <source>from <w src="H2603">2603</w> and <w src="H410">410</w>; favor of God;</source>

H2595.note: <note>lemma חֲניִת second vowel, corrected to חֲנִית</note>

H2600.meaning: <meaning><def>gratis</def>, i.e. devoid of cost, reason or advantage</meaning>
H2600.usage: <usage>without a cause (cost, wages), causeless, to cost nothing, free(-ly), innocent, for nothing (nought, in vain.</usage>

H2603.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>bend</def> or stoop in kindness to an inferior; to <def>favor</def>, <def>bestow</def>; causatively to <def>implore</def> (i.e. move to favor by petition)</meaning>
H2603.usage: <usage>beseech, × fair, (be, find, shew) favour(-able), be (deal, give, grant (gracious(-ly), intreat, (be) merciful, have (shew) mercy (on, upon), have pity upon, pray, make supplication, × very.</usage>

H2606.source: <source>from <w src="H2603">2603</w> and <w src="H410">410</w>; God has favored;</source>
H2606.meaning: <meaning><def>Chananel</def>, probably an Israelite, from whom a tower of Jerusalem was named</meaning>

H2608.source: <source>or <w pron="khan-an-yaw'-hoo" xlit="Chănanyâhûw">חֲנַנְיָהוּ</w>; from <w src="H2603">2603</w> and <w src="H3050">3050</w>; Jah has favored;</source>

H2614.meaning: <meaning>to <def>be narrow</def>; by implication, to <def>throttle</def>, or (reflex.) to <def>choke oneself to death</def> (by a rope)</meaning>

H2616.meaning: <meaning>properly, perhaps to <def>bow</def> (the neck only [compare <w src="H2603">2603</w>] in courtesy to an equal), i.e. to <def>be kind</def>; also (by euphemistically [compare <w src="H1288">1288</w>], but rarely) to <def>reprove</def></meaning>

H2617.meaning: <meaning><def>kindness</def>; by implication (towards God) <def>piety</def>; rarely (by opposition) <def>reproof</def>, or (subject.) <def>beauty</def></meaning>
H2617.usage: <usage>favour, good deed(-liness, -ness), kindly, (loving-) kindness, merciful (kindness), mercy, pity, reproach, wicked thing.</usage>
H2617.note: <note>lemma חֵסֵד both vowels; corrected to חֶסֶד</note>

H2619.source: <source>from <w src="H2617">2617</w> and <w src="H3050">3050</w>; Jah has favored;</source>

H2621.meaning: <meaning><def>Chosah</def>, an Israelite; also a place in Palestine</meaning>

H2627.source: <source>(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to <w src="H2637">2637</w>;</source>

H2635.source: <source>(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to that of <w src="H2636">2636</w>;</source>

H2636.source: <source>reduplicated from an unused root meaning apparently to <def>peel</def>;</source>

H2637.usage: <usage>be abated, bereave, decrease, (cause to) fail, (have) lack, make lower, want.</usage>

H2638.usage: <usage>destitute, fail, lack, have need, void, want.</usage>

H2643.source: <source>from <w src="H2653">2653</w> (in the moral sense of covered from soil);</source>

H2644.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>cover</def>, i.e. (in a sinister sense) to <def>act covertly</def></meaning>

H2648.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>start up suddenly</def>, i.e. (by implication) to <def>hasten away</def>, to <def>fear</def></meaning>

H2651.source: <source>from an unused root of uncertain signification;</source>

H2654.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>incline</def> to; by implication (literally but rarely) to <def>bend</def>; figuratively, to <def>be pleased</def> with, <def>desire</def></meaning>
H2654.usage: <usage>× any at all, (have, take) delight, desire, favour, like, move, be (well) pleased, have pleasure, will, would.</usage>

H2655.usage: <usage>delight in, desire, favour, please, have pleasure, whosoever would, willing, wish.</usage>

H2656.meaning: <meaning><def>pleasure</def>; hence (abstractly) <def>desire</def>; concretely, a <def>valuable</def> thing; hence (by extension) a <def>matter</def> (as something in mind)</meaning>
H2656.usage: <usage>acceptable, delight(-some), desire, things desired, matter, pleasant(-ure), purpose, willingly.</usage>

H2658.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>pry into</def>; by implication, to <def>delve</def>, to <def>explore</def></meaning>

H2659.source: <source>a primitive root (perhaps rather the same as <w src="H2658">2658</w> through the idea of <def>detection</def>);</source>
H2659.usage: <usage>be ashamed, be confounded, be brought to confusion (unto shame), come (be put to) shame, bring reproach.</usage>

H2660.source: <source>from <w src="H2658">2658</w> or <w src="H2659">2659</w>; a pit of shame;</source>
H2660.meaning: <meaning><def>Chepher</def>, a place in Palestine; also the name of three Israelites</meaning>

H2661.source: <source>from <w src="H2658">2658</w>; a <def>hole</def>; only in connection with <w src="H6512">6512</w>, which ought rather to be joined as one word, thus <w pron="khaf-ar-pay-raw'" xlit="chapharpêrâh">חַפַרְפֵּרָה</w>; by reduplication from <w src="H2658">2658</w>;</source>

H2664.meaning: <meaning>to <def>seek</def>; causatively, to <def>conceal oneself</def> (i.e. let be sought), or <def>mask</def></meaning>

H2669.source: <source>and <w pron="khof-sheeth'" xlit="chophshîyth">חׇפְשִׁית</w>; from <w src="H2666">2666</w>; (with <w src="H1004">1004</w>, a hospital)</source>

H2671.source: <source>from <w src="H2686">2686</w>; also by interchange for <w src="H6086">6086</w></source>
H2671.meaning: <meaning>properly, a <def>piercer</def>, i.e. an <def>arrow</def>; by implication, a <def>wound</def>; figuratively, (of God) thunder-<def>bolt</def>; the <def>shaft</def> of a spear</meaning>
H2671.usage: <usage>  archer, arrow, dart, shaft, staff, wound.</usage>

H2672.meaning: <meaning>to <def>cut</def> or carve (wood, stone or other material); by implication, to <def>hew</def>, <def>split</def>, <def>square</def>, <def>quarry</def>, <def>engrave</def></meaning>

H2675.source: <source>from <w src="H2674">2674</w> and a Aramaizing form of the feminine of <w src="H2319">2319</w> (compare <w src="H2323">2323</w>);</source>

H2677.usage: <usage>half, middle, mid(-night), midst, part, two parts.</usage>

H2679.source: <source>from <w src="H2677">2677</w> and the plural of <w src="H4496">4496</w>, with the article interposed; midst of the resting-places;</source>

H2682.source: <source>perhaps originally the same as <w src="H2681">2681</w>, from the <def>greenness</def> of a courtyard;</source>

H2683.source: <source>from an unused root meaning to hold firmly;</source>

H2684.source: <source>a collateral form of <w src="H2683">2683</w>, and meaning the same</source>

H2685.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>shear</def> or <def>cut close</def>; figuratively, to <def>be severe</def></meaning>

H2686.source: <source>a primitive root (compare <w src="H2673">2673</w>); also as denominative from <w src="H2671">2671</w></source>
H2686.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>chop</def> into, <def>pierce</def> or <def>sever</def>; hence, to <def>curtail</def>, to <def>distribute</def> (into ranks); to <def>shoot</def> an arrow</meaning>
H2686.usage: <usage>archer, × bands, cut off in the midst.</usage>

H2688.source: <source>or <w pron="khats-ats-one' taw-mawr'" xlit="Chatsătsôn Tâmâr">חַצֲצֹן תָּמָר</w>; from <w src="H2686">2686</w> and <w src="H8558">8558</w>; division (i.e. perhaps row) of (the) palm-tree;</source>

H2690.source: <source>a primitive root; properly, to surround with a stockade, and thus separate from the open country; but used only in the reduplicated form <w pron="khast-o-tsare'" xlit="chătsôtsêr">חֲצֹצֵר</w>; or (2 Chronicles 5:12) <w pron="khatso-rare'" xlit="chătsôrêr">חֲצֹרֵר</w>; as dem. from <w src="H2689">2689</w>;</source>

H2691.source: <source>(masculine and feminine); from <w src="H2690">2690</w> in its original sense;</source>

H2692.source: <source>from <w src="H2691">2691</w> and <w src="H146">146</w>; (the) village of Addar;</source>

H2693.source: <source>from <w src="H2691">2691</w> and a feminine of <w src="H1408">1408</w>; (the) village of (female) Fortune;</source>

H2694.source: <source>from <w src="H2691">2691</w> and <w src="H8484">8484</w> with the article interposed; village of the middle;</source>

H2695.source: <source>by an orthographical variation for <w src="H2696">2696</w>; enclosure;</source>

H2696.meaning: <meaning><def>Chetsron</def>, the name of a place in Palestine; also of two Israelites</meaning>

H2700.source: <source>from <w src="H2691">2691</w> and <w src="H4194">4194</w>; village of death;</source>

H2701.source: <source>from <w src="H2691">2691</w> and <w src="H5484">5484</w>; village of cavalry;</source>

H2702.source: <source>from <w src="H2691">2691</w> and the plural of <w src="H5483">5483</w>; village of horses;</source>

H2703.source: <source>from <w src="H2691">2691</w> and a derivative of <w src="H5869">5869</w>; village of springs;</source>

H2704.source: <source>from <w src="H2691">2691</w> and the same as <w src="H5881">5881</w>; village of springs;</source>

H2705.source: <source>from <w src="H2691">2691</w> and <w src="H7776">7776</w>; village of (the) fox;</source>

H2706.meaning: <meaning>an <def>enactment</def>; hence, an <def>appointment</def> (of time, space, quantity, labor or usage)</meaning>
H2706.usage: <usage>appointed, bound, commandment, convenient, custom, decree(-d), due, law, measure, × necessary, ordinance(-nary), portion, set time, statute, task.</usage>

H2708.source: <source>feminine of <w src="H2706">2706</w>, and meaning substantially the same</source>

H2709.source: <source>from an unused root probably meaning to bend; crooked;</source>

H2710.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>hack</def>, i.e. <def>engrave</def> (Judges 5:14, to <def>be a scribe</def> simply); by implication, to <def>enact</def> (laws being <def>cut</def> in stone or metal tablets in primitive times) or (gen.) <def>prescribe</def></meaning>

H2715.meaning: <meaning>properly, <def>white</def> or <def>pure</def> (from the <def>cleansing</def> or <def>shining</def> power of fire); hence (figuratively) <def>noble</def> (in rank)</meaning>

H2716.source: <source>from an unused (and vulgar) root probably meaning to <def>evacuate</def> the bowels;</source>

H2717.usage: <usage>decay, (be) desolate, destroy(-er), (be) dry (up), slay, × surely, (lay, lie, make) waste.</usage>

H2719.meaning: <meaning><def>drought</def>; also a <def>cutting</def> instrument (from its <def>destructive</def> effect), as a <def>knife</def>, <def>sword</def>, or other sharp implement</meaning>

H2722.meaning: <meaning><def>Choreb</def>, a (generic) name for the Sinaitic mountains</meaning>

H2727.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>leap suddenly</def>, i.e. (by implication) to <def>be dismayed</def></meaning>

H2729.meaning: <meaning>to <def>shudder</def> with terror; hence, to <def>fear</def>; also to <def>hasten</def> (with anxiety)</meaning>
H2729.usage: <usage>be (make) afraid, be careful, discomfit, fray (away), quake, tremble.</usage>

H2733.source: <source>patrial from a derivative of <w src="H2729">2729</w> (compare <w src="H5878">5878</w>);</source>

H2734.meaning: <meaning>to <def>glow</def> or <def>grow warm</def>; figuratively (usually) to <def>blaze up</def>, of anger, zeal, jealousy</meaning>
H2734.usage: <usage>be angry, burn, be displeased, × earnestly, fret self, grieve, be (wax) hot, be incensed, kindle, × very, be wroth. See <w src="H8474">8474</w>.</usage>

H2735.source: <source>from <w src="H2356">2356</w> and a collateral (masculine) form of <w src="H1412">1412</w>, with the article interposed; hole of the cleft;</source>

H2736.source: <source>; from <w src="H2734">2734</w> and <w src="H3050">3050</w>; fearing Jah;</source>

H2737.source: <source>from an unused root meaning to perforate;</source>
H2737.meaning: <meaning>properly, <def>pierced</def>, i.e. a <def>bead of pearl</def>, <def>gems</def> or <def>jewels</def> (as strung)</meaning>

H2738.source: <source>or (shortened) <w pron="khaw-rool'" xlit="chârul">חָרֻל</w>; apparently, a passive participle of an unused root probably meaning to be prickly;</source>
H2738.meaning: <meaning>properly, <def>pointed</def>, i.e. a <def>bramble</def> or other thorny weed</meaning>

H2739.source: <source>from passive participle of <w src="H2763">2763</w> and <w src="H639">639</w>; snub-nosed;</source>

H2741.source: <source>a patrial from (probably) a collateral form of <w src="H2756">2756</w>;</source>
H2741.meaning: <meaning><def>a Charuphite</def> or inhabitant of Charuph (or Chariph)</meaning>

H2742.source: <source>or <w pron="khaw-roots'" xlit="châruts">חָרֻץ</w>; passive participle of <w src="H2782">2782</w>;</source>
H2742.meaning: <meaning>properly, <def>incised</def> or (active) <def>incisive</def>; hence (as noun masculine or feminine) a <def>trench</def> (as dug), <def>gold</def> (as mined), a <def>threshing-sledge</def> (having sharp teeth); (figuratively) <def>determination</def>; also <def>eager</def></meaning>
H2742.usage: <usage>decision, diligent, (fine) gold, pointed things, sharp, threshing instrument, wall.</usage>

H2745.source: <source>from the same as <w src="H2775">2775</w>; perhaps shining;</source>

H2753.source: <source>or <w pron="kho-ree'" xlit="Chôwrîy">חוֹרִי</w>; the same as <w src="H2752">2752</w>;</source>

H2754.source: <source>or <w pron="khaw-reet'" xlit="châriṭ">חָרִט</w>; from the same as <w src="H2747">2747</w>;</source>

H2755.source: <source>from the plural of <w src="H2716">2716</w> and the plural of <w src="H3123">3123</w>; or perhaps rather the plural of a single word <w pron="khar-aw-yone'" xlit="chărâʼyôwn">חֲרָאיוֹן</w>, probably a kind of vegetable</source>

H2757.meaning: <meaning>properly, <def>incisure</def> or (passively) <def>incised</def>; hence, a <def>threshing-sledge</def> (with sharp teeth); also a <def>slice</def> (as cut)</meaning>

H2759.source: <source>from <w src="H2790">2790</w> in the sense of silence;</source>
H2759.meaning: <meaning><def>quiet</def>, i.e. <def>sultry</def> (as feminine noun, the sirocco or hot east wind)</meaning>

H2760.meaning: <meaning>to <def>braid</def> (i.e. to entangle or snare) or <def>catch</def> (game) <def>in a net</def></meaning>

H2761.source: <source>(Aramaic) a root probably allied to the equivalent of <w src="H2787">2787</w>;</source>

H2763.meaning: <meaning>to <def>seclude</def>; specifically (by a ban) to <def>devote to religious uses</def> (especially destruction); physical and reflexive, to <def>be blunt as to the nose</def></meaning>
H2763.usage: <usage>make accursed, consecrate, (utterly) destroy, devote, forfeit, have a flat nose, utterly (slay, make away).</usage>

H2764.meaning: <meaning>physical (as shutting in) a <def>net</def> (either literally or figuratively); usually a <def>doomed object</def>; abstractly <def>extermination</def></meaning>
H2764.usage: <usage>(ac-) curse(-d, -d thing), dedicated thing, things which should have been utterly destroyed, (appointed to) utter destruction, devoted (thing), net.</usage>

H2771.meaning: <meaning><def>Charan</def>, the name of a man and also of a place</meaning>

H2773.source: <source>dual of a derivative from <w src="H2356">2356</w>; <def>double cave-town</def>;</source>

H2775.source: <source>or (with a directive enclitic) <w pron="khar'-saw" xlit="charçâh">חַרְסָה</w>; from an unused root meaning to scrape; also perhaps from the mediating idea of <w src="H2777">2777</w></source>

H2777.source: <source>from <w src="H2775">2775</w> (apparently in the sense of a red tile used for scraping);</source>

H2803.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>plait</def> or <def>interpenetrate</def>, i.e. (literally) to <def>weave</def> or (generally) to <def>fabricate</def>; figuratively, to <def>plot</def> or <def>contrive</def> (usually in a malicious sense); hence (from the mental effort) to <def>think</def>, <def>regard</def>, <def>value</def>, <def>compute</def></meaning>

H3556.meaning: <meaning>a <def>star</def> (as round or as shining); figuratively, a <def>prince</def></meaning>

H3557.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>keep in</def>; hence, to <def>measure</def>; figuratively, to <def>maintain</def> (in various senses)</meaning>
H3557.usage: <usage>(be able to, can) abide, bear, comprehend, contain, feed, forbearing, guide, hold(-ing in), nourish(-er), be present, make provision, receive, sustain, provide sustenance (victuals).</usage>

H3558.source: <source>from an unused root meaning to <def>store</def> away;</source>

H3559.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>be erect</def> (i.e. stand perpendicular); hence (causatively) to <def>set up</def>, in a great variety of applications, whether literal (<def>establish</def>, <def>fix</def>, <def>prepare</def>, <def>apply</def>), or figurative (<def>appoint</def>, <def>render sure</def>, <def>proper</def> or <def>prosperous</def>)</meaning>
H3559.usage: <usage>certain(-ty), confirm, direct, faithfulness, fashion, fasten, firm, be fitted, be fixed, frame, be meet, ordain, order, perfect, (make) preparation, prepare (self), provide, make provision, (be, make) ready, right, set (aright, fast, forth), be stable, (e-) stablish, stand, tarry, × very deed.</usage>

H3563.source: <source>from an unused root meaning to hold together;</source>
H3563.meaning: <meaning>a <def>cup</def> (as a container), often figuratively, a <def>lot</def> (as if a potion); also some unclean bird, probably an <def>owl</def> (perhaps from the cup-like cavity of its eye)</meaning>

H3564.source: <source>from an unused root meaning properly, to <def>dig</def> through;</source>

H3565.source: <source>from <w src="H3564">3564</w> and <w src="H6227">6227</w>; furnace of smoke;</source>

H3566.source: <source>or (Ezra 1:1 (last time),2) <w pron="ko'-resh" xlit="Kôresh">כֹּרֶשׁ</w>; from the Persian;</source>

H3568.meaning: <meaning><def>Cush</def> (or Ethiopia), the name of a son of Ham, and of his territory; also of an Israelite</meaning>

H3573.source: <source>apparently from <w src="H3572">3572</w> and the dual of <w src="H7564">7564</w>; Cushan of double wickedness;</source>

H3576.usage: <usage>fail, (be found a, make a) liar, lie, lying, be in vain.</usage>

H3581.source: <source>or (Daniel 11:6) <w pron="ko'-akh" xlit="kôwach">כּוֹחַ</w>; from an unused root meaning to be firm;</source>
H3581.meaning: <meaning><def>vigor</def>, literally (force, in a good or a bad sense) or figuratively (capacity, means, produce); also (from its hardiness) a <def>large lizard</def></meaning>
H3581.usage: <usage>ability, able, chameleon, force, fruits, might, power(-ful), strength, substance, wealth.</usage>

H3582.meaning: <meaning>to <def>secrete</def>, by act or word; hence (intensively) to <def>destroy</def></meaning>

H3584.usage: <usage>deceive, deny, dissemble, fail, deal falsely, be found liars, (be-) lie, lying, submit selves.</usage>

H3588.source: <source>a primitive particle (the full form of the prepositional prefix) indicating causal relations of all kinds, antecedent or consequent;</source>
H3588.meaning: <meaning>(by implication) very widely used as a <def>relative conjunction</def> or adverb (as below); often largely modified by other particles annexed</meaning>
H3588.usage: <usage>and,   (forasmuch, inasmuch, where-) as, assured(-ly),   but, certainly, doubtless,   else, even,   except, for, how, (because, in, so, than) that,   nevertheless, now, rightly, seeing, since, surely, then, therefore,   (al-) though,   till, truly,   until, when, whether, while, whom, yea, yet.</usage>

H3589.source: <source>from a primitive root meaning to strike;</source>

H3591.source: <source>from the same as <w src="H3589">3589</w>; (perhaps smaller than <w src="H2595">2595</w>)</source>

H3594.meaning: <meaning>properly, a <def>statue</def>, i.e. <def>idol</def>; but used (by euphemism) for some <def>heathen deity</def> (perhaps corresponding to Priapus or Baal-peor)</meaning>

H3595.source: <source>or <w pron="kee-yore'" xlit="kîyôr">כִּיֹּר</w>; from the same as <w src="H3564">3564</w>;</source>
H3595.meaning: <meaning>properly, something <def>round</def> (as <def>excavated</def> or <def>bored</def>), i.e. a chafing-<def>dish</def> for coals or a <def>caldron</def> for cooking; hence (from similarity of form) a <def>washbowl</def>; also (for the same reason) a <def>pulpit</def> or platform</meaning>

H3596.source: <source>or <w pron="kay-lah'-ee" xlit="kêlay">כֵּלַי</w>; from <w src="H3557">3557</w> in the sense of <def>withholding</def>;</source>

H3597.source: <source>from an unused root meaning to clap or strike with noise;</source>

H3599.meaning: <meaning>a <def>cup</def>; also a <def>bag</def> for money or weights</meaning>

H3600.source: <source>a form for <w src="H3564">3564</w> (only in the dual);</source>
H3600.meaning: <meaning>a <def>cooking range</def> (consisting of two parallel stones, across which the boiler is set)</meaning>

H3601.meaning: <meaning>literally a <def>director</def>, i.e. the <def>spindle</def> or <def>shank of a distaff</def>, by which it is twirled</meaning>

H3602.meaning: <meaning><def>just so</def>, referring to the previous or following context</meaning>
H3602.usage: <usage>after that (this) manner, this matter, (even) so, in such a case, thus.</usage>

H3603.meaning: <meaning>a <def>circle</def>, i.e. (by implication) a circumjacent tract or region, especially the <def>Ghor</def> or valley of the Jordan; also a (round) <def>loaf</def>; also a <def>talent</def> (or large [round] <def>coin</def>)</meaning>

H3605.meaning: <meaning>properly, the <def>whole</def>; hence, <def>all</def>, <def>any</def> or <def>every</def> (in the singular only, but often in a plural sense)</meaning>
H3605.usage: <usage>(in) all (manner, (ye)), altogether, any (manner), enough, every (one, place, thing), howsoever, as many as, (no-) thing, ought, whatsoever, (the) whole, whoso(-ever).</usage>

H3606.usage: <usage>all, any,   (forasmuch) as,   be-(for this) cause, every,   no (manner, -ne),   there (where) -fore,   though, what (where, who) -soever, (the) whole.</usage>

H3607.meaning: <meaning>to <def>restrict</def>, by act (<def>hold back</def> or <def>in</def>) or word (<def>prohibit</def>)</meaning>
H3607.usage: <usage>finish, forbid, keep (back), refrain, restrain, retain, shut up, be stayed, withhold.</usage>

H3609.source: <source>apparently from <w src="H3607">3607</w> and <w src="H1">1</w>; restraint of (his) father;</source>

H3610.source: <source>dual of <w src="H3608">3608</w> in the original sense of separation;</source>

H3611.source: <source>from an unused root means. to <def>yelp</def>, or else to <def>attack</def>;</source>

H3612.source: <source>perhaps a form of <w src="H3611">3611</w>, or else from the same root in the sense of forcible;</source>

H3613.meaning: <meaning><def>Caleb-Ephrathah</def>, a place in Egypt (if the text is correct)</meaning>

H3614.source: <source>probably by erroneous transcription for <w pron="kaw-lay-bee'" xlit="Kâlêbîy">כָּלֵבִי</w>; patronymically from <w src="H3612">3612</w>;</source>

H3615.usage: <usage>accomplish, cease, consume (away), determine, destroy (utterly), be (when... were) done, (be an) end (of), expire, (cause to) fail, faint, finish, fulfil, × fully, × have, leave (off), long, bring to pass, wholly reap, make clean riddance, spend, quite take away, waste.</usage>

H3617.usage: <usage>altogether, (be, utterly) consume(-d), consummation(-ption), was determined, (full, utter) end, riddance.</usage>

H3618.note: <note>lemma כַּלָה missing dagesh, corrected to כַּלָּה</note>

H3619.meaning: <meaning>a <def>bird-trap</def> (as furnished with a clap-stick or treadle to spring it); hence, a <def>basket</def> (as resembling a wicker cage)</meaning>

H3624.source: <source>from an unused root meaning to be complete;</source>

H3627.meaning: <meaning>something <def>prepared</def>, i.e. any <def>apparatus</def> (as an implement, utensil, dress, vessel or weapon)</meaning>
H3627.usage: <usage>armour(-bearer), artillery, bag, carriage,   furnish, furniture, instrument, jewel, that is made of, × one from another, that which pertaineth, pot,   psaltery, sack, stuff, thing, tool, vessel, ware, weapon,   whatsoever.</usage>

H3629.meaning: <meaning>a <def>kidney</def> (as an essential <def>organ</def>); figuratively, the <def>mind</def> (as the interior self)</meaning>

H3632.meaning: <meaning><def>complete</def>; as noun, the <def>whole</def> (specifically, a sacrifice <def>entirely consumed</def>); as adverb, <def>fully</def></meaning>
H3632.usage: <usage>all, every whit, flame, perfect(-ion), utterly, whole burnt offering (sacrifice), wholly.</usage>

H3637.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>wound</def>; but only figuratively, to <def>taunt</def> or <def>insult</def></meaning>
H3637.usage: <usage>be (make) ashamed, blush, be confounded, be put to confusion, hurt, reproach, (do, put to) shame.</usage>

H3638.meaning: <meaning><def>Kilmad</def>, a place apparently in the Assyrian empire</meaning>

H3641.source: <source>or <w pron="kal-nay'" xlit="Kalnêh">כַּלְנֵה</w>; also <w pron="kal-no'" xlit="Kalnôw">כַּלְנוֹ</w>; of foreign derivation;</source>
H3641.meaning: <meaning><def>Calneh</def> or <def>Calno</def>, a place in the Assyrian empire</meaning>

H3644.source: <source>or <w pron="kaw-mo'" xlit="kâmôw">כָּמוֹ</w>; a form of the prefix <def>k</def>, but used separately [compare <w src="H3651">3651</w>];</source>
H3644.usage: <usage>according to, (such) as (it were, well as), in comparison of, like (as, to, unto), thus, when, worth.</usage>

H3645.source: <source>or (Jeremiah 48:7) <w pron="kem-eesh'" xlit="Kᵉmîysh">כְּמִישׁ</w>; from an unused root meaning to <def>subdue</def>; the <def>powerful</def>;</source>

H3646.source: <source>from an unused root meaning to <def>store</def> up or <def>preserve</def>;</source>

H3648.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>intertwine</def> or <def>contract</def>, i.e. (by implication) to <def>shrivel</def> (as with heat); figuratively, to <def>be deeply affected with passion</def> (love or pity)</meaning>

H3649.meaning: <meaning>properly, an <def>ascetic</def> (as if shrunk with self-maceration), i.e. an <def>idolatrous priest</def> (only in plural)</meaning>

H3650.meaning: <meaning><def>obscuration</def> (as if from shrinkage of light), i.e. an eclipse (only in plural)</meaning>

H3651.meaning: <meaning>properly, <def>set upright</def>; hence (figuratively as adjective) <def>just</def>; but usually (as adverb or conjunction) <def>rightly</def> or <def>so</def> (in various applications to manner, time and relation; often with other particles)</meaning>
H3651.usage: <usage>  after that (this, -ward, -wards), as... as,   (for-) asmuch as yet,   be (for which) cause,   following, howbeit, in (the) like (manner, -wise), × the more, right, (even) so, state, straightway, such (thing), surely,   there (where) -fore, this, thus, true, well, × you.</usage>

H3653.source: <source>the same as <w src="H3651">3651</w>, used as a noun;</source>

H3654.source: <source>from <w src="H3661">3661</w> in the sense of fastening; (from infixing its sting; used only in plural (and irregular in Exodus 8:17,18; Hebrews 13:14))</source>

H3655.meaning: <meaning>to <def>address</def> by an additional name; hence, to <def>eulogize</def></meaning>

H3658.source: <source>from a unused root meaning to twang;</source>

H3663.source: <source>or <w pron="kenan-yaw'-hoo" xlit="Kᵉnanyâhûw">כְּנַנְיָהוּ</w>; from <w src="H3661">3661</w> and <w src="H3050">3050</w>; Jah has planted;</source>

H3665.usage: <usage>bring down (low), into subjection, under, humble (self), subdue.</usage>

H3666.source: <source>from <w src="H3665">3665</w> in the sense of folding (compare <w src="H3664">3664</w>);</source>

H3667.meaning: <meaning><def>Kenaan</def>, a son a Ham; also the country inhabited by him</meaning>

H3669.meaning: <meaning>a <def>Kenaanite</def> or inhabitant of Kenaan; by implication, a <def>pedlar</def> (the Canaanites standing for their neighbors the Ishmaelites, who conducted mercantile caravans)</meaning>

H3671.meaning: <meaning>an <def>edge</def> or <def>extremity</def>; specifically (of a bird or army) a <def>wing</def>, (of a garment or bedclothing) a <def>flap</def>, (of the earth) a <def>quarter</def>, (of a building) a <def>pinnacle</def></meaning>
H3671.usage: <usage>  bird, border, corner, end, feather(-ed), × flying,   (one an-) other, overspreading, × quarters, skirt, × sort, uttermost part, wing(-ed).</usage>

H3672.source: <source>or <w pron="kinneh'-reth" xlit="Kinnereth">כִּנֶּרֶת</w><note>lemma כִּנֶרֶת missing dagesh, corrected to כִּנֶּרֶת</note>; respectively plural and singular feminine from the same as <w src="H3658">3658</w>; perhaps harp-shaped;</source>

H3676.source: <source>apparently a contraction for <w src="H3678">3678</w>, but probably by erroneous transcription for <w src="H5251">5251</w></source>

H3680.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>plump</def>, i.e. <def>fill up</def> hollows; by implication, to <def>cover</def> (for clothing or secrecy)</meaning>
H3680.usage: <usage>clad self, close, clothe, conceal, cover (self), (flee to) hide, overwhelm. Compare <w src="H3780">3780</w>.</usage>

H3689.meaning: <meaning>properly, <def>fatness</def>, i.e. by implication (literally) the <def>loin</def> (as the seat of the leaf fat) or (generally) the <def>viscera</def>; also (figuratively) <def>silliness</def> or (in a good sense) <def>trust</def></meaning>

H3690.meaning: <meaning>in a good sense, <def>trust</def>; in a bad one, <def>silliness</def></meaning>
H3690.note: <note>lemma כְּסִלָה first two vowels, corrected to כִּסְלָה</note>

H3694.source: <source>feminine plural of passive participle of <w src="H3688">3688</w>; <def>fattened</def>;</source>

H3695.meaning: <meaning><def>Casluchim</def>, a people cognate to the Egyptians</meaning>

H3696.source: <source>from the feminine plural of <w src="H3689">3689</w> and <w src="H8396">8396</w>; flanks of Tabor;</source>

H3700.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>become pale</def>, i.e. (by implication) to <def>pine after</def>; also to <def>fear</def></meaning>

H3704.meaning: <meaning>a <def>cushion</def> or <def>pillow</def> (as covering a seat or bed)</meaning>

H3706.source: <source>(Aramaic) or <w pron="keh-eth'" xlit="kᵉʻeth">כְּעֶת</w>; (Aramaic), feminine of <w src="H3705">3705</w>;</source>

H3707.usage: <usage>be angry, be grieved, take indignation, provoke (to anger, unto wrath), have sorrow, vex, be wroth.</usage>

H3708.usage: <usage>anger, angry, grief, indignation, provocation, provoking, × sore, sorrow, spite, wrath.</usage>

H3709.meaning: <meaning>the <def>hollow hand</def> or <def>palm</def> (so of the paw of an animal, of the sole, and even of the bowl of a dish or sling, the handle of a bolt, the leaves of a palm-tree); figuratively, <def>power</def></meaning>
H3709.usage: <usage>branch,   foot, hand((-ful), -dle, (-led)), hollow, middle, palm, paw, power, sole, spoon.</usage>

H3713.meaning: <meaning>properly, a <def>cover</def>, i.e. (by implication) a <def>tankard</def> (or covered goblet); also <def>white frost</def> (as covering the ground)</meaning>

H3715.meaning: <meaning>a <def>village</def> (as covered in by walls); also a <def>young lion</def> (perhaps as covered with a mane)</meaning>

H3716.source: <source>feminine of <w src="H3715">3715</w>; the village (always with the art.);</source>

H3720.meaning: <meaning><def>hunger</def> (as making to stoop with emptiness and pain)</meaning>

H3722.meaning: <meaning>to <def>cover</def> (specifically with bitumen); figuratively, to <def>expiate</def> or <def>condone</def>, to <def>placate</def> or <def>cancel</def></meaning>
H3722.usage: <usage>appease, make (an atonement, cleanse, disannul, forgive, be merciful, pacify, pardon, purge (away), put off, (make) reconcile(-liation).</usage>

H3724.meaning: <meaning>properly, a <def>cover</def>, i.e. (literally) a <def>village</def> (as covered in); (specifically) <def>bitumen</def> (as used for coating), and the <def>henna plant</def> (as used for dyeing); figuratively, a <def>redemption-price</def></meaning>
H3724.usage: <usage>bribe, camphire, pitch, ransom, satisfaction, sum of money, village.</usage>

H3726.source: <source>from <w src="H3723">3723</w> and <w src="H5984">5984</w>, with the article interposed; village of the Ammonite;</source>

H3727.meaning: <meaning>a <def>lid</def> (used only of the <def>cover</def> of the sacred Ark)</meaning>

H3730.source: <source>or (Amos 9:1) <w pron="kaf-tore'" xlit="kaphtôwr">כַּפְתּוֹר</w>; probably from an unused root meaning to <def>encircle</def>;</source>
H3730.meaning: <meaning>a <def>chaplet</def>; but used only in an architectonic sense, i.e. the <def>capital</def> of a column, or a wreath-like <def>button</def> or <def>disk</def> on the candelabrum</meaning>

H3731.source: <source>or (Amos 9:7) <w pron="kaf-tore'" xlit="Kaphtôwr">כַּפְתּוֹר</w>; apparently the same as <w src="H3730">3730</w>;</source>
H3731.meaning: <meaning><def>Caphtor</def> (i.e. a wreath-shaped island), the original seat of the Philistines</meaning>

H3733.source: <source>from <w src="H3769">3769</w> in the sense of plumpness;</source>
H3733.meaning: <meaning>a <def>ram</def> (as full-grown and fat), including a <def>battering-ram</def> (as butting); hence, a <def>meadow</def> (as for sheep); also a <def>pad</def> or <def>camel's saddle</def> (as puffed out)</meaning>
H3733.usage: <usage>captain, furniture, lamb, (large) pasture, ram. See also <w src="H1033">1033</w>, <w src="H3746">3746</w>.</usage>

H3734.meaning: <meaning>properly, a deep round <def>vessel</def>, i.e. (specifically) a <def>cor</def> or measure for things dry</meaning>

H3735.source: <source>(Aramaic) probably corresponding to <w src="H3738">3738</w> in the sense of piercing(figuratively);</source>

H3737.source: <source>(Aramaic) from a verb corresponding to that of <w src="H3736">3736</w>;</source>

H3738.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>dig</def>; figuratively, to <def>plot</def>; generally, to <def>bore</def> or <def>open</def></meaning>

H3739.source: <source>usually assigned as a primitive root, but probably only a special application of <w src="H3738">3738</w> (through the common idea of planning implied in a bargain);</source>

H3746.source: <source>perhaps an abridged plural of <w src="H3733">3733</w> in the sense of leader (of the flock);</source>

H3754.source: <source>from an unused root of uncertain meaning;</source>
H3754.usage: <usage>vines, (increase of the) vineyard(-s), vintage. See also <w src="H1021">1021</w>.</usage>

H3755.source: <source>active participle of an imaginary denominative from <w src="H3754">3754</w>;</source>

H3759.meaning: <meaning>a planted <def>field</def> (garden, orchard, vineyard or park); by implication, garden <def>produce</def></meaning>

H3760.meaning: <meaning><def>Karmel</def>, the name of a hill and of a town in Palestine</meaning>

H3766.meaning: <meaning>to <def>bend</def> the knee; by implication, to <def>sink</def>, to <def>prostrate</def></meaning>
H3766.usage: <usage>bow (down, self), bring down (low), cast down, couch, fall, feeble, kneeling, sink, smite (stoop) down, subdue, × very.</usage>

H3767.meaning: <meaning>the <def>leg</def> (from the knee to the ankle) of men or locusts (only in the dual)</meaning>

H3772.meaning: <meaning>to <def>cut</def> (off, down or asunder); by implication, to <def>destroy</def> or <def>consume</def>; specifically, to <def>covenant</def> (i.e. make an alliance or bargain, originally by cutting flesh and passing between the pieces)</meaning>
H3772.usage: <usage>be chewed, be con-(feder-) ate, covenant, cut (down, off), destroy, fail, feller, be freed, hew (down), make a league (covenant), × lose, perish, × utterly, × want.</usage>

H3774.source: <source>probably from <w src="H3772">3772</w> in the sense of executioner; (compare <w src="H2876">2876</w>) (only collectively in the singular as plural)</source>

H3777.source: <source>from an unused root of uncertain meaning;</source>

H3778.source: <source>(occasionally with enclitic) <w pron="kas-dee'-maw" xlit="Kasdîymâh">כַּשְׂדִּימָה</w>; towards the Kasdites into Chaldea), patronymically from <w src="H3777">3777</w> (only in the plural);</source>
H3778.meaning: <meaning>a <def>Kasdite</def>, or descendant of Kesed; by implication, a Chaldaean (as if so descended); also an astrologer (as if proverbial of that people</meaning>

H3779.meaning: <meaning>a <def>Chaldaean</def> or inhabitant of Chaldaea; by implication, a Magian or professional astrologer</meaning>

H3782.meaning: <meaning>to <def>totter</def> or <def>waver</def> (through weakness of the legs, especially the ankle); by implication, to <def>falter</def>, <def>stumble</def>, <def>faint</def> or <def>fall</def></meaning>
H3782.usage: <usage>bereave (from the margin), cast down, be decayed, (cause to) fail, (cause, make to) fall (down, -ing), feeble, be (the) ruin(-ed, of), (be) overthrown, (cause to) stumble, × utterly, be weak.</usage>

H3784.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>whisper</def> a spell, i.e. to <def>inchant</def> or <def>practise magic</def></meaning>

H3787.source: <source>a primitive root properly, to be straight or right;</source>
H3787.meaning: <meaning>by implication, to <def>be acceptable</def>; also to <def>succeed</def> or <def>prosper</def></meaning>

H3789.meaning: <meaning>to <def>grave</def>, by implication, to <def>write</def> (describe, inscribe, prescribe, subscribe)</meaning>

H3793.meaning: <meaning>a <def>letter</def> or other <def>mark</def> branded on the skin</meaning>

H3794.source: <source>or <w pron="kit-tee-ee'" xlit="Kittîyîy">כִּתִּיִּי</w>; patrial from an unused name denoting Cyprus (only in the plural);</source>
H3794.meaning: <meaning>a <def>Kittite</def> or <def>Cypriote</def>; hence, an islander in general, i.e. the Greeks or Romans on the shores opposite Palestine</meaning>

H3796.source: <source>from an unused root meaning to compact;</source>

H3798.source: <source>from <w src="H3796">3796</w> and <w src="H376">376</w>; <def>wall of a man</def>;</source>
H3798.note: <note>lemma כְּתִלִישׁ first two vowels, corrected to כִּתְלִישׁ</note>

H4916.meaning: <meaning>a <def>sending</def> out, i.e. (abstractly) <def>presentation</def> (favorable), or <def>seizure</def> (unfavorable); also (concretely) a place of <def>dismissal</def>, or a <def>business</def> to be discharged</meaning>

H4917.meaning: <meaning>a <def>mission</def>, i.e. (abstractly and favorable) <def>release</def>, or (concretely and unfavorable) an <def>army</def></meaning>

H4920.source: <source>or <w pron="mesh-eh-lem-yaw'-hoo" xlit="Mᵉshelemyâhûw">מְשֶׁלֶמְיָהוּ</w>; from <w src="H7999">7999</w> and <w src="H3050">3050</w>; <def>ally of Jah</def>;</source>

H4924.meaning: <meaning><def>fat</def>, i.e. (literally and abstractly) <def>fatness</def>; but usually (figuratively and concretely) a <def>rich</def> dish, a <def>fertile</def> field, a <def>robust</def> man</meaning>

H4927.meaning: <meaning><def>Mishma</def>, the name of a son of Ishmael, and of an Israelite</meaning>

H4928.meaning: <meaning><def>audience</def>, i.e. the royal <def>court</def>; also <def>obedience</def>, i.e. (concretely) a <def>subject</def></meaning>

H4929.meaning: <meaning>a <def>guard</def> (the man, the post or the prison); a <def>deposit</def> (figuratively); also (as observed) a usage (abstractly), or an <def>example</def> (concretely)</meaning>

H4931.meaning: <meaning><def>watch</def>, i.e. the act (<def>custody</def>), or (concretely) the <def>sentry</def>, the <def>post</def>; objectively <def>preservation</def>, or (concretely) <def>safe</def>; figuratively <def>observance</def>, i.e. (abstractly) <def>duty</def> or (objectively) <def>a usage</def> or <def>party</def></meaning>
H4931.usage: <usage>charge, keep, or to be kept, office, ordinace, safeguard, ward, watch.</usage>

H4932.meaning: <meaning>properly, a <def>repetition</def>, i.e. a <def>duplicate</def> (<def>copy</def> of a document), or a <def>double</def> (in amount); by implication, a <def>second</def> (in order, rank, age, quality or location)</meaning>
H4932.usage: <usage>college, copy, double, fatlings, next, second (order), twice as much.</usage>

H4940.meaning: <meaning>a <def>family</def>, i.e. <def>circle of relatives</def>; figuratively, a <def>class</def> (of persons), a <def>species</def> (of animals) or <def>sort</def> (of things); by extension a <def>tribe</def> or <def>people</def></meaning>

H4941.meaning: <meaning>properly, a <def>verdict</def> (favorable or unfavorable) pronounced judicially, especially a <def>sentence</def> or formal decree (human or (participant's) divine <def>law</def>, individual or collective), including the act, the place, the suit, the crime, and the penalty; abstractly, <def>justice</def>, including a participant's <def>right</def> or <def>privilege</def> (statutory or customary), or even a <def>style</def></meaning>
H4941.usage: <usage>  adversary, ceremony, charge, × crime, custom, desert, determination, discretion, disposing, due, fashion, form, to be judged, judgment, just(-ice, -ly), (manner of) law(-ful), manner, measure, (due) order, ordinance, right, sentence, usest, × worthy,   wrong.</usage>

H4945.meaning: <meaning>properly, <def>causing to drink</def>, i.e. a <def>butler</def>; by implication (intransitively), <def>drink</def> (itself); figuratively, a <def>well-watered</def> region</meaning>

H4947.source: <source>from <w src="H8259">8259</w> in its original sense of overhanging;</source>

H4949.source: <source>or <w pron="mish-ko'-leth" xlit="mishqôleth">מִשְׁקֹלֶת</w>; feminine of <w src="H4948">4948</w> or <w src="H4947">4947</w>;</source>

H4953.source: <source>(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to <w src="H8319">8319</w>;</source>

H4954.source: <source>patrial from an unused noun from an unused root; probably meaning to <def>stretch out</def>; <def>extension</def>;</source>

H4956.source: <source>from the plural of <w src="H4955">4955</w> and <w src="H4325">4325</w>; <def>burnings of water</def>;</source>

H4958.source: <source>apparently from an unused root meaning to <def>perforate</def>, i.e. <def>hollow out</def>;</source>

H4960.meaning: <meaning><def>drink</def>, by implication, <def>drinking</def> (the act); also (by implication) a <def>banquet</def> or (generally) <def>feast</def></meaning>

H4962.meaning: <meaning>properly, an <def>adult</def> (as of full length); by implication, a <def>man</def> (only in the plural)</meaning>

H4965.source: <source>from <w src="H4964">4964</w> and <w src="H520">520</w> with the art. interposed; bit of the metropolis;</source>

H4967.source: <source>from <w src="H4962">4962</w> and <w src="H410">410</w>, with the relative interposed; man who (is) of God;</source>

H4968.source: <source>from <w src="H4962">4962</w> and <w src="H7973">7973</w>; <def>man of a dart</def>;</source>

H4970.source: <source>from an unused root meaning to extend;</source>
H4970.meaning: <meaning>properly, <def>extent</def> (of time); but used only adverbially (especially with other particle prefixes), <def>when</def> (either relative or interrogative)</meaning>

H4971.source: <source>or <w pron="math-koo'-neth" xlit="mathkuneth">מַתְכֻנֶת</w>; from <w src="H8505">8505</w> in the transferred sense of measuring;</source>

H4975.source: <source>from an unused root meaning to <def>be slender</def>;</source>
H4975.meaning: <meaning>properly, the <def>waist</def> or small of the back; only in plural the <def>loins</def></meaning>

H4977.meaning: <meaning><def>Mattan</def>, the name of a priest of Baal, and of an Israelite</meaning>

H4979.meaning: <meaning>a <def>present</def>; specifically (in a good sense), a <def>sacrificial offering</def>, (in a bad sense) a <def>bribe</def></meaning>

H4981.source: <source>probably patrial from an unused noun meaning slenderness;</source>

H4983.source: <source>or <w pron="mat-tan-yaw'-hoo" xlit="Mattanyâhûw">מַתַּנְיָהוּ</w>; from <w src="H4976">4976</w> and <w src="H3050">3050</w>; <def>gift of Jah</def>;</source>

H4993.source: <source>or <w pron="mat-tith-yaw'-hoo" xlit="Mattithyâhûw">מַתִּתְיָהוּ</w>; from <w src="H4991">4991</w> and <w src="H3050">3050</w>; <def>gift of Jah</def>;</source>

H4994.source: <source>a primitive particle of incitement and entreaty, which may usually be rendered;</source>
H4994.meaning: <meaning><def>'I pray'</def>, <def>'now'</def>, or <def>'then'</def>; added mostly to verbs (in the Imperative or Future), or to interjections, occasionally to an adverb or conjunction</meaning>
H4994.usage: <usage>I beseech (pray) thee (you), go to, now, oh.</usage>

H4995.source: <source>apparently from <w src="H5106">5106</w> in the sense of harshness from refusal;</source>

H4996.meaning: <meaning><def>No</def> (i.e. Thebes), the capital of Upper Egypt</meaning>

H4997.source: <source>or <w pron="node" xlit="nʼôwd">נאוֹד</w><note>lemma נֹאוד vowel, corrected to נאוֹד</note><note>xlit nôʼwd corrected to nʼôwd</note>; also (feminine) <w pron="no-daw'" xlit="nôʼdâh">נֹאדָה</w>; from an unused root of uncertain signification;</source>

H4998.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>be at home</def>, i.e. (by implication) to be <def>pleasant</def> (or <def>suitable</def>), i.e. <def>beautiful</def></meaning>

H5001.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>whisper</def>, i.e. (by implication) to <def>utter</def> as an oracle</meaning>

H5003.usage: <usage>adulterer(-ess), commit(-ing) adultery, woman that breaketh wedlock.</usage>

H5006.meaning: <meaning>to <def>scorn</def>; or (in Ecclesiastes 12:5), by interchange for <w src="H5132">5132</w>, to <def>bloom</def></meaning>
H5006.usage: <usage>abhor, (give occasion to) blaspheme, contemn, despise, flourish, × great, provoke.</usage>

H5012.meaning: <meaning>to <def>prophesy</def>, i.e. <def>speak</def> (or sing) <def>by inspiration</def> (in prediction or simple discourse)</meaning>

H5015.meaning: <meaning><def>Nebo</def>, the name of a Babylonian deity, also of a mountain in Moab, and of a place in Palestine</meaning>

H5019.source: <source>or <w pron="neb-oo-kadnets-tsar'" xlit="Nᵉbukadneʼtstsar">נְבֻּכַדְנֶאצַּר</w>; (2 Kings 24:1,10), or <w pron="neb-oo-kad-nets-tsar'" xlit="Nᵉbûwkadnetstsar">נְבוּכַדְנֶצַּר</w>; (Esther 2:6; Daniel 1:18), or <w pron="neb-oo-kad-rets-tsar'" xlit="Nᵉbûwkadreʼtstsar">נְבוּכַדְרֶאצַּר</w>; or <w pron="neb-oo-kadrets-tsore'" xlit="Nᵉbûwkadreʼtstsôwr">נְבוּכַדְרֶאצּוֹר</w>; (Ezra 2:1; Jeremiah 49:28), or foreign derivation;</source>

H5022.source: <source>feminine plural from the same as <w src="H5011">5011</w>; <def>fruits</def>;</source>

H5025.meaning: <meaning><def>Nobach</def>, the name of an Israelite, and of a place East of the Jordan</meaning>

H5027.meaning: <meaning>to <def>scan</def>, i.e. <def>look intently at</def>; by implication, to <def>regard</def> with pleasure, favor or care</meaning>
H5027.usage: <usage>(cause to) behold, consider, look (down), regard, have respect, see.</usage>

H5031.meaning: <meaning>a <def>prophetess</def> or (generally) <def>inspired</def> woman; by implication, a <def>poetess</def>; by association a <def>prophet's wife</def></meaning>

H5032.source: <source>or <w pron="neb-aw-yoth'" xlit="Nᵉbâyôth">נְבָיֹת</w>; feminine plural from <w src="H5107">5107</w>; <def>fruitfulnesses</def>;</source>
H5032.meaning: <meaning><def>Nebajoth</def>, a son of Ismael, and the country settled by him</meaning>

H5033.source: <source>from an unused root meaning to <def>burst forth</def>;</source>

H5034.meaning: <meaning>to <def>wilt</def>; generally, to <def>fall</def> away, <def>fail</def>, <def>faint</def>; figuratively, to <def>be foolish</def> or (morally) <def>wicked</def>; causatively, to <def>despise</def>, <def>disgrace</def></meaning>
H5034.usage: <usage>disgrace, dishounour, lightly esteem, fade (away, -ing), fall (down, -ling, off), do foolishly, come to nought, × surely, make vile, wither.</usage>

H5035.meaning: <meaning>a skin-<def>bag</def> for liquids (from <def>collapsing</def> when empty); hence, a <def>vase</def> (as similar in shape when full); also a <def>lyre</def> (as having a body of like form)</meaning>

H5038.meaning: <meaning>a <def>flabby</def> thing, i.e. a <def>carcase</def> or <def>carrion</def> (human or bestial, often collectively); figuratively, an <def>idol</def></meaning>
H5038.usage: <usage>(dead) body, (dead) carcase, dead of itself, which died, (beast) that (which) dieth of itself.</usage>

H5042.meaning: <meaning>to <def>gush forth</def>; figuratively, to <def>utter</def> (good or bad words); specifically, to <def>emit</def> (a foul odor)</meaning>
H5042.usage: <usage>belch out, flowing, pour out, send forth, utter (abundantly).</usage>

H5043.source: <source>(Aramaic) from an unused root meaning to shine;</source>

H5045.source: <source>from an unused root meaning to be parched;</source>
H5045.meaning: <meaning>the <def>south</def> (from its drought); specifically, the <def>Negeb</def> or southern district of Judah, occasionally, <def>Egypt</def> (as south to Palestine)</meaning>

H5046.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>front</def>, i.e. stand boldly out opposite; by implication (causatively), to <def>manifest</def>; figuratively, to <def>announce</def> (always by word of mouth to one present); specifically, to <def>expose</def>, <def>predict</def>, <def>explain</def>, <def>praise</def></meaning>
H5046.usage: <usage>bewray, × certainly, certify, declare(-ing), denounce, expound, × fully, messenger, plainly, profess, rehearse, report, shew (forth), speak, × surely, tell, utter.</usage>

H5047.meaning: <meaning>to <def>flow</def> (through the idea of clearing the way)</meaning>

H5048.meaning: <meaning>a <def>front</def>, i.e. <def>part opposite</def>; specifically a <def>counterpart</def>, or <def>mate</def>; usually (adverbial, especially with preposition) <def>over against</def> or <def>before</def></meaning>
H5048.usage: <usage>about, (over) against, × aloof, × far (off), × from, over, presence, × other side, sight, × to view.</usage>

H5055.meaning: <meaning>to <def>butt</def> with the horns; figuratively, to <def>war</def> against</meaning>

H5057.meaning: <meaning>a <def>commander</def> (as occupying the <def>front</def>), civil, military or religious; generally (abstractly, plural), <def>honorable</def> themes</meaning>
H5057.usage: <usage>captain, chief, excellent thing, (chief) governor, leader, noble, prince, (chief) ruler.</usage>

H5058.meaning: <meaning>properly, <def>instrumental music</def>; by implication, a <def>stringed instrument</def>; by extension, a <def>poem set to music</def>; specifically, an <def>epigram</def></meaning>

H5059.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>thrum</def>, i.e. <def>beat</def> a tune with the fingers; expectation. to <def>play</def> on a stringed instrument; hence (generally), to <def>make music</def></meaning>
H5059.usage: <usage>player on instruments, sing to the stringed instruments, melody, ministrel, play(-er, -ing).</usage>

H5060.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>touch</def>, i.e. <def>lay the hand upon</def> (for any purpose; euphemistically, to lie with a woman); by implication, to <def>reach</def> (figuratively, to <def>arrive</def>, <def>acquire</def>); violently, to <def>strike</def> (punish, defeat, destroy, etc.)</meaning>
H5060.usage: <usage>beat, (× be able to) bring (down), cast, come (nigh), draw near (nigh), get up, happen, join, near, plague, reach (up), smite, strike, touch.</usage>

H5061.meaning: <meaning>a <def>blow</def> (figuratively, infliction); also (by implication) a <def>spot</def> (concretely, a leprous person or dress)</meaning>

H5062.usage: <usage>beat, dash, hurt, plague, slay, smite (down), strike, stumble, × surely, put to the worse.</usage>

H5064.meaning: <meaning>to <def>flow</def>; figuratively, to <def>stretch out</def>; causatively, to <def>pour out</def> or <def>down</def>; figuratively, to <def>deliver over</def></meaning>
H5064.usage: <usage>fall, flow away, pour down (out), run, shed, spilt, trickle down.</usage>

H5065.meaning: <meaning>to <def>drive</def> (an animal, a workman, a debtor, an army); by implication, to <def>tax</def>, <def>harass</def>, <def>tyrannize</def></meaning>
H5065.usage: <usage>distress, driver, exact(-or), oppress(-or), × raiser of taxes, taskmaster.</usage>

H5066.meaning: <meaning>to <def>be</def> or <def>come</def> (causatively, <def>bring</def>) <def>near</def> (for any purpose); euphemistically, to <def>lie with</def> a woman; as an enemy, to <def>attack</def>; religious to <def>worship</def>; causatively, to <def>present</def>; figuratively, to <def>adduce</def> an argument; by reversal, to <def>stand back</def></meaning>
H5066.usage: <usage>(make to) approach (nigh), bring (forth, hither, near), (cause to) come (hither, near, nigh), give place, go hard (up), (be, draw, go) near (nigh), offer, overtake, present, put, stand.</usage>

H5067.source: <source>from <w src="H5110">5110</w> in the sense of <def>piling</def> up;</source>

H5068.meaning: <meaning><def>to impel</def>; hence, <def>to volunteer</def> (as a soldier), <def>to present spontaneously</def></meaning>
H5068.usage: <usage>offer freely, be (give, make, offer self) willing(-ly).</usage>

H5071.meaning: <meaning>properly (abstractly) <def>spontaneity</def>, or (adjectively) <def>spontaneous</def>; also (concretely) a <def>spontaneous</def> or (by inference, in plural) <def>abundant</def> gift</meaning>
H5071.usage: <usage>free(-will) offering, freely, plentiful, voluntary(-ily, offering), willing(-ly), offering).</usage>

H5073.source: <source>(Aramaic) from a root meaning to stick;</source>

H5074.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>wave</def> to and fro (rarely to flap up and down); figuratively, to <def>rove</def>, <def>flee</def>, or (causatively) to <def>drive away</def></meaning>
H5074.usage: <usage>chase (away), × could not, depart, flee (× apace, away), (re-) move, thrust away, wander (abroad, -er, -ing).</usage>

H5077.source: <source>or <w pron="nawdaw'" xlit="nâdâʼ">נָדָא</w>; (2 Kings 17:21), a primitive root;</source>

H5078.source: <source>from <w src="H5077">5077</w> in the sense of freely flinging money;</source>

H5079.meaning: <meaning>properly, <def>rejection</def>; by implication, <def>impurity</def>, especially personal (menstruation) or moral (idolatry, incest)</meaning>
H5079.usage: <usage>× far, filthiness, × flowers, menstruous (woman), put apart, × removed (woman), separation, set apart, unclean(-ness, thing, with filthiness).</usage>

H5080.meaning: <meaning>to push <def>off</def>; used in a great variety of applications, literally and figuratively (to expel, mislead, strike, inflict, etc.)</meaning>
H5080.usage: <usage>banish, bring, cast down (out), chase, compel, draw away, drive (away, out, quite), fetch a stroke, force, go away, outcast, thrust away (out), withdraw.</usage>

H5081.meaning: <meaning>properly, <def>voluntary</def>, i.e. generous; hence, <def>magnanimous</def>; as noun, a <def>grandee</def> (sometimes a <def>tyrant</def>)</meaning>

H5083.source: <source>probably from an unused root meaning to <def>give</def>;</source>

H5085.meaning: <meaning>a <def>sheath</def>; figuratively, the <def>body</def> (as the receptacle of the soul)</meaning>

H5086.usage: <usage>drive (away, to and fro), thrust down, shaken, tossed to and fro.</usage>

H5087.meaning: <meaning>to <def>promise</def> (pos., to do or give something to God)</meaning>

H5090.meaning: <meaning>to <def>drive</def> forth (a person, an animal or chariot), i.e. <def>lead</def>, <def>carry away</def>; reflexively, to <def>proceed</def> (i.e. impel or guide oneself); also (from the <def>panting</def> induced by effort), to <def>sigh</def></meaning>
H5090.usage: <usage>acquaint, bring (away), carry away, drive (away), lead (away, forth), (be) guide, lead (away, forth).</usage>

H5091.meaning: <meaning>to <def>groan</def>, i.e. <def>bewail</def>; hence (through the idea of crying aloud), to <def>assemble</def> (as if on proclamation)</meaning>

H5094.source: <source>(Aramaic) or <w pron="neh-hee-roo'" xlit="nᵉhîyrûw">נְהִירוּ</w>; (Aramaic), from the same as <w src="H5105">5105</w>;</source>

H5095.meaning: <meaning>properly, to run with a <def>sparkle</def>, i.e. <def>flow</def>; hence (transitively), to <def>conduct</def>, and (by inference) to <def>protect</def>, <def>sustain</def></meaning>

H5096.source: <source>or <w pron="nah-halole'" xlit="Nahălôl">נַהֲלֹל</w>; the same as <w src="H5097">5097</w>;</source>

H5102.meaning: <meaning>to <def>sparkle</def>, i.e. (figuratively) <def>be cheerful</def>; hence (from the <def>sheen</def> of a running stream) to <def>flow</def>, i.e. (figuratively) <def>assemble</def></meaning>

H5103.source: <source>(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to <w src="H5102">5102</w>;</source>

H5104.meaning: <meaning>a <def>stream</def> (including the sea; expectation the Nile, Euphrates, etc.); figuratively, <def>prosperity</def></meaning>

H5106.usage: <usage>break, disallow, discourage, make of none effect.</usage>

H5110.meaning: <meaning>to <def>nod</def>, i.e. <def>waver</def>; figuratively, to <def>wander</def>, <def>flee</def>, <def>disappear</def>; also (from shaking the head in sympathy), to <def>console</def>, <def>deplore</def>, or (from tossing the head in scorn) <def>taunt</def></meaning>
H5110.usage: <usage>bemoan, flee, get, mourn, make to move, take pity, remove, shake, skip for joy, be sorry, vagabond, way, wandering.</usage>

H5112.note: <note>lemma נוֹדּ extra dagesh, corrected to נוֹד</note>

H5115.meaning: <meaning>to <def>rest</def> (as at home); causatively (through the implied idea of <def>beauty</def>), to <def>celebrate</def> (with praises)</meaning>

H5116.meaning: <meaning>(adjectively) <def>at home</def>; hence (by implication of satisfaction) <def>lovely</def>; also (noun) a <def>home</def>, of God (temple), men (residence), flocks (pasture), or wild animals (<def>den</def>)</meaning>
H5116.usage: <usage>comely, dwelling (place), fold, habitation, pleasant place, sheepcote, stable, tarried.</usage>

H5117.meaning: <meaning>to <def>rest</def>, i.e. <def>settle</def> down; used in a great variety of applications, literal and figurative, intransitive, transitive and causative (to <def>dwell</def>, <def>stay</def>, <def>let fall</def>, <def>place</def>, <def>let alone</def>, <def>withdraw</def>, <def>give comfort</def>, etc.)</meaning>
H5117.usage: <usage>cease, be confederate, lay, let down, (be) quiet, remain, (cause to, be at, give, have, make to) rest, set down. Compare <w src="H3241">3241</w>.</usage>

H5122.source: <source>(Aramaic) or <w pron="nev-aw-lee'" xlit="nᵉvâlîy">נְוָלִי</w>; (Aramaic), from an unused root probably meaning to be foul;</source>

H5125.meaning: <meaning>to <def>resprout</def>, i.e. <def>propagate by shoots</def>; figuratively, to <def>be perpetual</def></meaning>

H5127.meaning: <meaning>to <def>flit</def>, i.e. <def>vanish</def> away (subside, escape; causatively, chase, impel, deliver)</meaning>
H5127.usage: <usage>× abate, away, be displayed, (make to) flee (away, -ing), put to flight, × hide, lift up a standard.</usage>

H5128.meaning: <meaning>to <def>waver</def>, in a great variety of applications, literally and figuratively (as subjoined)</meaning>
H5128.usage: <usage>continually, fugitive, × make, to (go) up and down, be gone away, (be) move(-able, -d), be promoted, reel, remove, scatter, set, shake, sift, stagger, to and fro, be vagabond, wag, (make) wander (up and down).</usage>

H5129.source: <source>from <w src="H3259">3259</w> and <w src="H3050">3050</w>; convened of Jah;</source>
H5129.meaning: <meaning><def>Noadjah</def>, the name of an Israelite, and a false prophetess</meaning>

H5130.meaning: <meaning>to <def>quiver</def> (i.e. <def>vibrate</def> up and down, or <def>rock</def> to and fro); used in a great variety of applications (including sprinkling, beckoning, rubbing, bastinadoing, sawing, waving, etc.)</meaning>
H5130.usage: <usage>lift up, move, offer, perfume, send, shake, sift, strike, wave.</usage>

H5132.meaning: <meaning>properly, to <def>flash</def>; also, to <def>fly</def> away (from the quickness of motion)</meaning>

H8586.meaning: <meaning><def>caprice</def> (as a fit <def>coming on</def>), i.e. <def>vexation</def>; concretely a <def>tyrant</def></meaning>

H8593.meaning: <meaning>a <def>knife</def> or <def>razor</def> (as <def>making</def> bare); also a <def>scabbard</def> (as <def>being bare</def>, i.e. empty)</meaning>

H8597.usage: <usage>beauty(-iful), bravery, comely, fair, glory(-ious), honour, majesty.</usage>

H8599.meaning: <meaning><def>Tappuach</def>, the name of two places in Palestine, also of an Israelite</meaning>

H8610.meaning: <meaning>to <def>manipulate</def>, i.e. <def>seize</def>; chiefly to <def>capture</def>, <def>wield</def>, specifically, to <def>overlay</def>; figuratively, to <def>use unwarrantably</def></meaning>

H8615.usage: <usage>expectation(-ted), hope, live, thing that I long for.</usage>

H8628.meaning: <meaning>to <def>clatter</def>, i.e. <def>slap</def> (the hands together), <def>clang</def> (an instrument); by analogy, to <def>drive</def> (a nail or tent-pin, a dart, etc.); by implication, to <def>become bondsman</def> by handclasping)</meaning>
H8628.usage: <usage>blow (a trumpet), cast, clap, fasten, pitch (tent), smite, sound, strike, × suretiship, thrust.</usage>

H8643.meaning: <meaning><def>clamor</def>, i.e. <def>acclamation</def> of joy or a <def>battle-cry</def>; especially <def>clangor</def> of trumpets, as an <def>alarum</def></meaning>
H8643.usage: <usage>alarm, blow(-ing) (of, the) (trumpets), joy, jubile, loud noise, rejoicing, shout(-ing), (high, joyful) sound(-ing).</usage>

H8644.source: <source>from <w src="H7322">7322</w> in the sense of its congener <w src="H7495">7495</w>;</source>

H8645.meaning: <meaning>a species of tree (apparently from its <def>slenderness</def>), perhaps the <def>cypress</def></meaning>
